{"session_id":"svc-1783129016725656235","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-07-04T01:36:59.581031232Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-438d7ee3-20260704T013528-2b9d720c","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` metadata and wire `parent -\u0026gt; child`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-438d7ee3\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebeads: add structured cross-repo blocker ref field + known-repos config + validation\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;There is no structured way to record which repo+bead a status=blocked bead is waiting on. Only free-text ExternalBlockerReason exists (cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go:12, cli/internal/bead/store.go:761).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go and cli/internal/bead/store.go model status=blocked with a single free-text reason field only; cli/internal/config/types.go:21-50 (NewConfig) has no place to register other repos by name.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX (see docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-040-cross-repo-blocker-recheck.md §2-3 for full contract)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/store.go: add const ExtraLifecycleCrossRepoBlockerRef = \u0026#34;lifecycle-cross-repo-blocker-ref\u0026#34;, storing JSON {\u0026#34;repo\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026lt;name\u0026gt;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;bead\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;\u0026#34;} in Bead.Extra, alongside (not replacing) ExtraLifecycleExternalBlockerReason.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/config/types.go: add KnownRepos map[string]KnownRepoConfig to NewConfig, where KnownRepoConfig has Path string (local, mutually exclusive with Node+Project) and Node/Project string (federation node_id/project_id per ADR-007).\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/bead.go: add --blocked-by-ref \u0026lt;repo\u0026gt;#\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; flag to `ddx bead update --status blocked`. Parse format (single \u0026#39;#\u0026#39;, non-empty repo, non-empty bead-id); on parse failure return a hard error (not silently dropped). Validate \u0026lt;repo\u0026gt; exists as a key in the loaded known-repos config; on unknown repo return a hard error naming the repo.\u0026#xA;- ExternalBlockerReason remains required for status=blocked regardless of whether --blocked-by-ref is also set (lifecycle.go:122 unchanged).\u0026#xA;- `ddx bead show \u0026lt;id\u0026gt; --json` must surface the parsed ref via the existing Extra passthrough (no new top-level JSON field).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- No recheck command or auto-reopen logic (child beads 2 and 3 of ddx-3b5ab8aa).\u0026#xA;- No federation query implementation, only the config schema shape for node/project entries.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/bead/store.go defines ExtraLifecycleCrossRepoBlockerRef and a helper to marshal/unmarshal the {repo,bead} JSON shape, covered by TestCrossRepoBlockerRef_RoundTrip in cli/internal/bead/store_test.go.\u0026#xA;2. cli/internal/config/types.go adds KnownRepos map[string]KnownRepoConfig to NewConfig with Path and Node/Project fields, covered by TestConfig_KnownRepos_Unmarshal in cli/internal/config/types_test.go (or nearest existing config test file) asserting a known-repos YAML block round-trips.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;id\u0026gt; --status blocked --external-blocker-reason \u0026#34;...\u0026#34; --blocked-by-ref \u0026lt;repo\u0026gt;#\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;` sets the structured Extra field only when \u0026lt;repo\u0026gt; is a known-repos key, and returns a non-zero exit with a clear error naming the bad input for: malformed ref (missing \u0026#39;#\u0026#39;, empty repo, empty bead-id) and unknown repo. Covered by TestBeadUpdate_BlockedByRef_Validation in cli/cmd/bead_test.go (table test enumerating: valid ref, malformed ref, unknown repo, missing external-blocker-reason with only --blocked-by-ref set).\u0026#xA;4. `ddx bead show \u0026lt;id\u0026gt; --json` includes the parsed ref object under Extra for a bead created via AC3\u0026#39;s valid case, asserted in the same or a companion test in cli/cmd/bead_test.go.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... ./internal/config/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:beads, area:lifecycle, kind:feature, td:TD-040\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"9fc3b9f72d83872df1915de8b5fbf8ec55be4761\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260704T013528-2b9d720c\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID":"20260704T013528-2b9d720c","DDX_BEAD_DIR":"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx/.ddx","DDX_BEAD_ID":"ddx-438d7ee3","DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-438d7ee3-20260704T013528-2b9d720c/.ddx/executions/20260704T013528-2b9d720c/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-438d7ee3-20260704T013528-2b9d720c/.ddx/executions/20260704T013528-2b9d720c/embedded/git-bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.codex/tmp/arg0/codex-arg0Yu4YDA:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/erik/.local/sha